                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.4111 Eden, Anthony/1<hi rend="superscript"
                        >3/5</hi>: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-18T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 18, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 18—11:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1246. My telegram number 1171, February 15, 9 p.m. I learn that in addition to
                    those mentioned Strang<note n="14" xml:id="d7fn14">William Strang, British
                        Assistant Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> will likewise
                    accompany Mr. Eden. In mentioning this Sir Orme Sargent<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d7fn15">British Deputy Under Secretary of State for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> expressed some little anxiety less [<hi rend="italic"
                        >lest</hi>] the size and composition of Mr. Eden’s party might lead to
                    public expectations on both sides of the Atlantic that important negotiations
                    are on foot and subsequent disappointment and harmful speculation when no great
                    tangible results of the talks in Washington can be announced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
